Poland was 50 years in communism, Russia 70. 
In Poland there were some private sectors (agriculture and small business)
Poland has more manufacturing for consumers, Russia had heavy industry and military sector. Finally, many Rusian cities have just one enterprise and were totally dependent on this enterprise.
